# Tournament logic

## Schedules

Matrices live in [`src/schedules.js`](src/schedules.js) as player-slot templates (1–8). Resolve names via `getActualSchedule`. Changing one count’s matrix must not alter another. Round flags:

- `addSecondRound`, `addThirdRound`, `addFourthRound` (multi-round 4–5 player flows)

## Scoring and winners

Wins and net points are **derived** from `gameScores` in [`src/scoring.js`](src/scoring.js) (`computePlayerResults`). Do not reintroduce parallel sticky win/point counters. Sort: **wins descending**, then **net points descending**.

Editing a score removes that game from `gameScores` then re-adds; totals recompute automatically.

## Sticky keys (do not rename casually)

**App:** `playercount`, `playersAreSubmitted`, `players`, `addSecondRound`, `addThirdRound`, `addFourthRound`, `gameScores`

**GameCard (per game):** `inputScore{gameNo}`, `isButtonPressed{gameNo}`

Shared hook: [`src/hooks/useStickyState.js`](src/hooks/useStickyState.js) (safe JSON.parse).

Submit Score requires both team scores to be non-empty digits.

When changing schedules or scoring, follow the `verify-tournament` skill checklist.
